spanGrp.span: I think that as for the Cabecars,
Ys t (m) begetse se je k'wak kabekar-wa
and those in our place, there are many of us and we are alike.
sa k' ska se r eb t'
People think that we are different,
pe t begetse n se r kww
but the Indians themselves know that we are the same.
wakwa jegeta *t [w] jur jebi se r eb
We may speak differently; they speak differently and we speak differently;
Se je kt-'g jebn (_) (_) (_) se je kt'-g r jaul
There are clans there that we do not know.
Ma/ jeska dist ts ka sul se je w jiebi
It is said that we are not better than they are,
Jeska wayi-n ka r kuna jie-wa cha r je k se je cha inga
nor that we are better than them;
o se je cha k jie-wa cha inga
but it was God, not us, who separated us.
ataran Sib n t sa jula bts jekepi ka r se je w se je wakwa jula bts jebi
God blew on us with his breath
Sib t se je (_) se je wkw' y jie siw' wa
he just made corn and black corn.
And so he spread them across the earth.
Jebi jie t j'-m jishg inga
but there is nothing that can change us.
Pero ka jir kuna t sa wmnw kww bi kuna
Se r e-kka u/ e-kka ua b
Just because of that people think that we do not underestand each other,
(_) Jebn wa pe t begetse-n ka se ksr- ra je ra je kt r kww
but it is the same language;
it is the same and it has the same name.
they speak well and we speak well too;
jem jie-wa kt'-g r b se je kt'-g r b
we do not outdo them but they do not outdo us.
Jie-wa ka kt' don se je m jie-wa ka kt' don se je m y ka se je don jie-wa
it was God who let us the way he wanted.
Sib n t sa wagi ka/ sa wak katatik-ka menbi jie-wa kiar kepi
And we cannot change that and be only one.
Jeska ka se mn je (_) kt' menw-glu-m e-kka ua b kuna
